13. Use FlatButton Widget in Flutter App Development

The FlatButton widget in Flutter is used to create a simple button without elevation (flat design).
It is typically used for less important actions in the UI.


⚠️ Note: FlatButton is deprecated in newer Flutter versions and replaced by TextButton, but it is still asked in exams.

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: FlatButtonExample(),
    );
  }
}

class FlatButtonExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("FlatButton Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: FlatButton(
          onPressed: () {
            print("FlatButton Clicked");
          },
          color: Colors.blue,
          textColor: Colors.white,
          child: Text("Click Me"),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
